EXIProcessor - Class in cl.clayster.exi
This class containes several methods and fields to be used for encoding and decoding using the EXI compression method.
EXIProcessor(EXISetupConfiguration) - Constructor for class cl.clayster.exi.EXIProcessor
Constructs an EXI Processor using xsdLocation as the Canonical Schema and the respective parameters in exiConfig for its configuration.
EXISetupConfiguration - Class in cl.clayster.exi
Contains all relevant values to setup EXI compression options in order to propose them to the server and use them for compresses communication according to the XEP-0322 protocol.
EXISetupConfiguration() - Constructor for class cl.clayster.exi.EXISetupConfiguration
Constructs a new EXISetupConfigurations and initializes it with Default Values.
exists() - Method in class cl.clayster.exi.EXISetupConfiguration
Checks if the configuration given has been used before, in order to know if quick setup configurations can be used.
EXIXMPPConnection - Class in cl.clayster.exi
Defines necessary methods to establish an EXI connection over XMPP as specified in XEP-0322.
EXIXMPPConnection(ConnectionConfiguration, EXISetupConfiguration) - Constructor for class cl.clayster.exi.EXIXMPPConnection
This constructor uses the given EXISetupConfiguration to negotiate EXI compression while logging in.
